rComments: Such a horrible lecturer. If you already have an understanding of course material before coming in, you should be good. If you don't, you will not learn anything. His lectures are SO boring, and if you ask him a question in office hours, he goes on a 5 minute tangent not related to your question. He's nice though. Had him for 250 and 410

His lectures are pretty typical for an IR class, but you can tell he clearly finds the topics fascinating, which is nice, and he is always available to give help. i've had him as a teacher/ta twice, for trn250 and trn410, and John is truly a gem. One of the kindest, knowledgeable professors i've come across. Would recommend his class.

The worst professor that barely teaches anything. He definitely has some good aspects for sure (like being available via email and office hours). However, his lectures are SO BORING AND UNENGAGING. If you're already good, then you'll be fine in his class as his grading isn't that tough. However, if you're not yet and are trying to learn, then no.
john is a wonderful ta and professor. if you pay attention, and do the work, you will do fine, and he always makes himself available to help.

Dirks is a wonderful prof. He used to be a TA for TRN250, and he's now doing a great job w/ the course. His voice is painfully monotone, and you may fall asleep. But he makes extra effort to be available to students in office hours, and responds promptly to e-mails. Plus, the grading in his courses isn't too tough compared to other IR classes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']
